Floyd C. Wilson: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg










































  





















































































July 29, 2017 1:35 AM ET
Oil, Gas and Consumable Fuels

Company Overview of Halcón Resources Corporation



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Floyd C. Wilson  Chairman of the Board, Chief Executive Officer & President, Halcón Resources CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships70$24,124,696As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Floyd C. Wilson has been the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Halcón Resources Corporation since February 2012 and as its President since September 9, 2016. Mr. Wilson serves as the Chief Executive Officer of HK Resources, LLC and The 7711 Corporation. He serves as the Chief Executive Officer of Halcón Louisiana Operating, L.P. Mr. Wilson serves as Chief Executive Officer at Halcón Energy Properties, Inc. He has been Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President ... of Halcon Resources, LLC since February 9, 2012. He has been Chief Executive Officer and Director of GeoResources, Inc. since August 1, 2012. Mr. Wilson served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of BHP Billiton Petroleum (KCS Resources), LLC. Mr. Wilson served as the Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of Halres LLC since February 09, 2012. He served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of 3TEC Energy Corporation from August 1999 to June 2003. He served as the President of Halcón Resources Corporation until May 16, 2012. He served as the Chief Executive Officer, President and Chairman of the Board of Petrohawk Management Company LLC, a General Partner of HK Energy Partners GP LP - General Partner of HK Energy Partners LP since October 2007. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Petrohawk Energy Corporation from May 25, 2004 to August 24, 2011. He served as the President of Petrohawk Energy Corporation from May 25, 2004 to September 2009. He was an Owner of PHAWK LLC which he founded in June 2003 and served as its President and Chief Executive Officer. He served as the Chief Executive Officer, President, Chairman of Beta Oil & Gas Inc. since May 2004. Mr. Wilson founded in 1987 and served as President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of the Board of Hugoton Energy Corp. since Hugoton Energy Corp.'s inception in 1987. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of 3TEC from August 1999 to its merger with Plains Exploration & Production Company in June of 2003. He served as Manager of Enex Resources Corp. He began his career in the energy business in Houston in 1970 as a Production Engineer. He moved to Wichita, Kansas in 1976 to start an oil and gas company, one of several private energy ventures he founded and later sold. He joined 3TEC Energy Corporation on August 27, 1999, concurrent with the investment in 3TEC Energy Corp. by W/E Energy Company L.L.C., formerly known as 3TEC Energy Company L.L.C. (“W/E“). In 1994, Mr. Wilson took Houston public and sold it in 1998 to Chesapeake Energy Corporation. In 1994, Hugoton completed an initial public offering and was merged into Chesapeake Energy Corporation in 1998. He founded W/E Energy Company L.L.C., (formerly known as 3TEC Energy Company L.L.C.) in 1998 and served as its President until August 1999. He served as Chairman of Petrohawk Energy Corporation from May 25, 2004 to August 25, 2011. He serves as a member of the Board of Directors of the Kansas Independent Oil and Gas Association. He served as a Director of 3TEC Energy Corporation since 1999; Hugoton Energy Corp. since 1987; Beta Oil & Gas Inc.; and Petrohawk Energy corporation from June 2003 to August 25, 2011.Read Full Background




